    "node": {
      "id": "0830853c-9dec-52c0-a9e8-90b1c3357af6",
      "wordpress_id": 2317,
      "link": "https://www.slightedgecoder.com/2018/12/18/page-not-found-on-netlify-with-react-router/",
      "slug": "page-not-found-on-netlify-with-react-router",
      "status": "publish",
      "template": "",
      "format": "standard",
      "jetpack_featured_media_url": "https://i2.wp.com/www.slightedgecoder.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/featured-image-4.jpg?fit=600%2C402&ssl=1",
      "content": "\n<p style=\"text-align:right\"><em>Photo by¬†</em><a href=\"https://unsplash.com/photos/MAgPyHRO0AA?utm_source=unsplash&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_content=creditCopyText\"><em>Hello I&#8217;m Nik</em></a><em>¬†on¬†</em><a href=\"https://unsplash.com/search/photos/direction?utm_source=unsplash&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_content=creditCopyText\"><em>Unsplash</em></a></p>\n\n\n\n<p>You might run into the following error after deploying a single page React site using React Router to Netlify.</p>\n\n\n\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p><strong>Page Not Found</strong></p><p>Looks like you&#8217;ve followed a broken link or entered a URL that doesn&#8217;t exist on this site.</p></blockquote>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://i2.wp.com/www.slightedgecoder.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/page-not-found.jpg?w=1170&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-2318\" srcset=\"https://i2.wp.com/www.slightedgecoder.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/page-not-found.jpg?w=916&amp;ssl=1 916w, https://i2.wp.com/www.slightedgecoder.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/page-not-found.jpg?resize=300%2C133&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i2.wp.com/www.slightedgecoder.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/page-not-found.jpg?resize=768%2C340&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i2.wp.com/www.slightedgecoder.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/page-not-found.jpg?resize=585%2C259&amp;ssl=1 585w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 916px) 100vw, 916px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" /><figcaption>Error message on Netlify</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<!--more-->\n\n\n\n<h2><br>How did the error occur?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>React Router handles routing on the client side (browser) so when you visit non-root page (e.g. <code>https://yoursite.netlify.com/else</code>), Netlify (server-side) does not know how to handle the route.<br><em>(As your routes are set up in the root level).</em></p>\n\n\n\n<h2><br>Error Code &amp; Demo</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Here is the simplest code using React Router.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-coblocks-gist\"><script src=\"https://gist.github.com/dance2die/fae8d963496b66dc2d23f5605d478976.js\"></script><noscript><a href=\"https://gist.github.com/dance2die/fae8d963496b66dc2d23f5605d478976\">View this gist on GitHub</a></noscript></div>\n\n\n\n<p>And the error occurring on Netlify when you go to¬†<code>https://&lt;netlify domain>/else</code> directly.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://i1.wp.com/www.slightedgecoder.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/page-not-found.gif?w=1170&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-2322\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\"/><figcaption>Page Not Found Demo</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2><br>How can we fix it?</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Netlify offers a special file, <a href=\"https://www.netlify.com/docs/redirects/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\"Netlify offers a special file, _redirects, which you can add to your code base and let Netlify handle how to handle the URL that is not handled on the client-side. (opens in a new tab)\">_redirects</a>, which you can add to your code base and let Netlify handle how to handle the URL that is not handled on the client-side.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em>Netlify documentation has a section, </em><a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\"Netlify documentation has a section, History Pushstate and Single Page Apps, which shows you how to¬† (opens in a new tab)\" href=\"https://www.netlify.com/docs/redirects/#history-pushstate-and-single-page-apps\" target=\"_blank\"><em>History Pushstate and Single Page Apps</em></a><em>, which shows you how to redirect to the root of your SPA URL (but doesn&#8217;t mention React Router, as it applies to other client-side frameworks/libraries).</em></p>\n\n\n\n<p>So to fix the issue, we need to create a file named <code>_redirects</code> to the root of your site with following content.</p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-coblocks-gist\"><script src=\"https://gist.github.com/dance2die/acf9a148ec8025364bf0b6cf37367294.js\"></script><noscript><a href=\"https://gist.github.com/dance2die/acf9a148ec8025364bf0b6cf37367294\">View this gist on GitHub</a></noscript></div>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://i1.wp.com/www.slightedgecoder.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/redirect-on-CodeSandbox.png?w=1170&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-2327\" srcset=\"https://i1.wp.com/www.slightedgecoder.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/redirect-on-CodeSandbox.png?w=507&amp;ssl=1 507w, https://i1.wp.com/www.slightedgecoder.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/redirect-on-CodeSandbox.png?resize=300%2C190&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 507px) 100vw, 507px\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\" /><figcaption>_redirect static file</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><em>Change¬†</em><code><em>index.html</em></code><em>¬†accordingly to match the SPA root.</em></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Here is the <a href=\"https://react-router-v4-to-deploy-to-netlify-with-redirects.netlify.com/else\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\"Here is the working site. (opens in a new tab)\">working site</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://i2.wp.com/www.slightedgecoder.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/page-found.gif?w=1170&#038;ssl=1\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-2331\" data-recalc-dims=\"1\"/><figcaption>Netlify successfully redirected to the SPA root</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p style=\"text-align:right\"><em>For more ways &amp; restrictions for redirect, check out </em><a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\"For more ways to redirect on Netlify, check out the official documentation. (opens in a new tab)\" href=\"https://www.netlify.com/docs/redirects/\" target=\"_blank\"><em>the official Netlify documentation</em></a><em>.</em></p>\n\n\n\n<h2><br>Resources</h2>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Where I found out the answer &#8211;¬†<a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\"Where I found out the answer -¬†How do you handle frontend routing with Netlify and React Router v4? on Reddit.‚Ä®Source code with _redirects file.‚Ä®Source code¬†without¬†_redirects¬†file.‚Ä®Netlify site with _redirects file.‚Ä®Netlify site without _redirects file. (opens in a new tab)\" href=\"https://www.reddit.com/r/Frontend/comments/6h34h0/how_do_you_handle_frontend_routing_with_netlify/\" target=\"_blank\">How do you handle frontend routing with Netlify and React Router v4?</a> on Reddit.</li><li><a href=\"https://www.netlify.com/docs/redirects/#history-pushstate-and-single-page-apps\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\"Where I found out the answer -¬†How do you handle frontend routing with Netlify and React Router v4? on Reddit.‚Ä®_redirects Netlify documentation for SPA.‚Ä®Source code with _redirects file.‚Ä®Source code¬†without¬†_redirects¬†file.‚Ä®Netlify site with _redirects file.‚Ä®Netlify site without _redirects file. (opens in a new tab)\">_redirects Netlify documentation</a> for SPA.</li><li><a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\"Source code with _redirects file. (opens in a new tab)\" href=\"https://codesandbox.io/s/o5q81vvljz\" target=\"_blank\">Source code</a> with <code>_redirects</code> file.</li><li><a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\"Source code with _redirects file.‚Ä®Source code¬†without¬†_redirects¬†file. (opens in a new tab)\" href=\"https://codesandbox.io/s/w2p29jj0jl\" target=\"_blank\">Source code</a>¬†with<strong>out</strong>¬†<code>_redirects</code>¬†file.</li><li><a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\"Source code with _redirects file.‚Ä®Source code¬†without¬†_redirects¬†file.‚Ä®Netlify site with _redirects file.‚Ä®Netlify site without _redirects file. (opens in a new tab)\" href=\"https://react-router-v4-to-deploy-to-netlify-with-redirects.netlify.com/else\" target=\"_blank\">Netlify site</a> with _redirects file.</li><li><a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" aria-label=\"Source code with _redirects file.‚Ä®Source code¬†without¬†_redirects¬†file.‚Ä®Netlify site with _redirects file.‚Ä®Netlify site without _redirects file. (opens in a new tab)\" href=\"https://react-router-v4-to-deploy-to-netlify-without-redirects.netlify.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Netlify site</a> with<strong>out</strong> _redirects file.</li></ul>\n",
